<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean manufacturers said that a severe economic
slump will appear in February despite signs of domestic currency
market stabilization, according to a survey issued by the
Federation of Korean Industries (FKI) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
