<HEADLINE> France Calls on US to Suspend Execution of Tucker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 3 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine today called on the United States to suspend the execution
of Karla Tucker, a 38-year-old woman convicted of murder and is
scheduled to be executed this evening in the Huntsville prison,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the government of Texas will decide to suspend
this execution," said Vedrine when answering a question at the
National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
The governor of Texas, George Bush Jr., or the U.S. Supreme
Court, can stop the execution at the last moment.
</P>
<P>
France abolished death penalty in 1981, soon after President
Francois Mitterrand came to power. 
</P>
