<HEADLINE> C'Wealth Fund to Invest More in African States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 3 (Xinhua) -- The Commonwealth Africa
Investment Fund (Comafin) Tuesday announced that a total of 20
projects have already been approved in principle mainly in
Zambia, Uganda, Tanzania, South Africa and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Comafin said in a statement released here that the investments
were mainly in the sectors of telecommunications and other
infrastructure, agri-business, property development and
manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The projects included an establishment of a farm in Uganda for
which it would provide three million U.S. Dollars, and an
intensive farming business in Zambia for which it would invest up
to 2.5 million U.S. Dollars for 24 percent of the share capital.
</P>
<P>
The Comafin also agreed to provide 40,000 U.S. Dollars to help
fund the preparation of a full business plan, and agreed in
principle to a further investment of four million Dollars for its
implementation.
</P>
<P>
The investment portfolio included the Harare Airport Gateway
Ltd and Lake Harvest Ltd. The Harare airport gateway project
aimed to develop a 109 hectares export processing zone adjacent
to the Harare international airport, providing facilities for
airport-related high technology industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
