<DOCNO> XIE19980204.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets Swiss Federal Councillor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERN, Switzerland, February 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice Premier
Li Lanqing met here today with Swiss Federal Councillor and
Minister of Finance Kaspar Villiger.
</P>
<P>
The two were satisfied with the two countries' relationship of
friendship and cooperation and agreed that constant exchanges of
visits at a high level had vigorously promoted the development of
mutual relations.
</P>
<P>
Li said that since the establishment of foreign relations in
1950, the relationship between China and Switzerland has been
developed in an overall smooth way. The Sino-Swiss relationship
has been closer and closer in recent years, he added.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have maintained a good political relationship
and broadened their economic relationship day after day, Li said.
There has been also satisfactory progress in cooperation of
finance, science and technology, an education, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Villiger said that the relationship between Switzerland and
China is extremely good and the relationship is of two-fold
friends. The Swiss government is fully confident in the further
development of the two countries' relationship of friendship and
cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li and Villiger exchanged views on further developing and
strengthening cooperation in the trade and economic relations
between the two countries. They pointed out with satisfaction that
such relations are in a trend of continuous development.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Switzerland and China are complementary in economy
and have bright prospects in strengthening their cooperation in
trade and economy.
</P>
<P>
Villiger said that China has been implementing opening-up
policies and its national economy has been in rapid growth. The
establishment of an investment fund for Swiss joint ventures in
China will guarantee further cooperation between small and medium
sized companies between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
On China's entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO),
Villiger said, China has made great efforts in aspects like market
access. The Swiss government fully supports China's early
accession to the multilateral trade system, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Villiger on China's principles and a series of
efforts for its entry into the WTO and thanked Villiger for the
Swiss government's support for China in this aspect and hoped that
Switzerland will continue to play an active role. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
