<DOCNO> XIE19980204.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Church Leaders to Meet in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 3 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the World
Council of Churches (WCC) reverend Konrad Raiser will visit
Zimbabwe in March to assess the preparations of the 8th assembly
of the WCC to be held here on December 3-14.
</P>
<P>
WCC Administrative Assistance Busi Nhliziyo said here Tuesday
that Raiser was expected to meet Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe and formally invite him to the assembly, which is held
every seven years.
</P>
<P>
The assembly, to be held for the second time in Africa, will
coincide with jubilee celebrations to mark WCC's 50 years of
existence.
</P>
<P>
Africa hosted the assembly in 1975 for the first time in
Nairobi, Kenya. 
</P>
</TEXT>
