<HEADLINE> UNDP Supports Uganda in Fighting Against Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 3 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) is providing 200,000 U.S. dollars to
help the government and the people of Uganda cope with cholera and
other emergencies thought to be caused by the El Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
A release from UNDP said an estimated 400 people have died so
far from cholera, which has spread to 18 Ugandan districts and is
being blamed on poor sanitation and incessant rains.
</P>
<P>
The funding will help strengthen logistical coordination,
distribute disinfectants and gloves and carry out a public
information campaign.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains have disrupted the already vulnerable livelihoods
of people in many parts of Uganda, some losing their homes and
other property. UNDP assistance will also be used to improve
disaster readiness and responses at the district level. 
</P>
