<HEADLINE> Canada Ratifies NATO Enlargement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien announced today that his country has ratified amendments
to the North Atlantic Treaty which admits three new members to
NATO next year.
</P>
<P>
Canada is the first NATO member to take this step. Foreign
Affairs Minister Lloyd Axworthy signed the instrument of
ratification Monday night.
</P>
<P>
"In being the first NATO member to ratify the amendments, we
have shown the importance we attach to integrating the countries
of central and eastern Europe into the security framework of the
Trans-Atlantic community," Chretien noted.
</P>
<P>
Poland, Hungary and the Czech Republic are expected to be
admitted to full NATO membership in April 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
