<HEADLINE> Annan Calls Aziz to Talk About Iraq Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 3 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today telephoned Iraq's Deputy Prime Minister Tareq
Aziz and they discussed the growing crisis over Iraq's weapons
inspection, UN spokesman Eckhard Fred said today.
</P>
<P>
"They discussed the seriousness of the situation and the need
to get results," Eckhard told reporters at the noon briefing.
</P>
<P>
"The secretary-general initiated the talks and described the
conversation as `constructive.' They agreed on the need to speed
up efforts to find a negotiated solution to the problem," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Eckhard said the UN chief also spoke by telephone to Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak about the Arab League's plans to send its
Secretary-General Esmat Abdel-Meguid to Iraq Wednesday in an
effort to defuse the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The UN secretary-general told the Security Council Monday that
he was standing ready to offer his good office to resolve the
crisis over Iraq's weapons inspection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
