<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Set up National Desertification Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced Tuesday
that a national desertification fund will be set up so as to back
up the efforts underway in the country to curtain the phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made at a workshop organized here by the
Environmental Protection Authority to discuss the setting up of
the fund.
</P>
<P>
According to the authority, the Ethiopian government will
formulate a national plan of action for the fight against
desertification.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the workshop, Minister of Agriculture Seyfu Ketema
said the fund to be set up on legal grounds is indispensable to
achieve sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is closely following the process in
pipeline for the formation of the fund and its success.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Development Fund (UNDP) is providing
financial and technical support for the realization of the
national fund, according to the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
