<HEADLINE> Armenian President Announces Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 3 (Xinhua) -- President of Armenia Levon
Ter-Petrosyan announced his resignation at the national television
this evening, the Itar-Tass news agency reported from Yerevan,
capital of Armenia.
</P>
<P>
The president's resignation came in the wake of a political
crisis in the solution of the Nagorno-Karabakh problem, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Ter-Petrosyan's resignation was preceded by a string of
resignations of officials close to the president.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the president accepted the resignation submitted
by Yerevan mayor Vano Siradegyan, head of the ruling Armenian
National Movement.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Ter-Petrosyan relieved Alexander Arzumanyan of the
post of minister of foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
Besides, it was announced today that resignation was sought by
Minister for Territorial Administration Galust Gamazyan, Central
Bank governor Bagrat Asatryan and Director of the Executive Board
of the National Fund "Armenia" Manushak Petrosyan, whose
resignation was accepted by the president earlier.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here hold that a serious divergence over the solution
of the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict has led to a political crisis in
the Caucasus republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
