<HEADLINE> Finland Announces New Funding to Combat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, february 3 (Xinhua) -- The government of
Finland has announced a new contribution of about 750,000 U.S.
dollars for the United Nations Development Program (UNDP)'s
Trust Fund to Combat Desertification and Drought.
</P>
<P>
A release from UNDP said today Finland made an earlier
contribution of 288,279 dollars to the fund. The new funding will
support UNDP's newly developed strategy and action plan to promote
the role of women in decision-making processes in the
implementation of the Convention to Combat Desertification.
</P>
<P>
It will also enable UNDP to assist countries of the
Commonwealth of Independence States in the development and
implementation of national and sub-regional action programs to
prevent desertification and drought.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 1.7 billion people in developing countries live in
drylands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
