<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-03 19:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Rightists Vandalize Rabin's Memorial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Israelis Tuesday cleaned up
the memorial for late prime minister Yitzhak Rabin, which has been
vandalized by rightists.
</P>
<P>
Monday night, Jewish extremists painted sentences of "Rabin is
a traitor" and "Rabin is a murderer" on the memorial erected last
year.
</P>
<P>
The outlawed rightist Kach Movement claimed responsibility for
the action, which was condemned by politicians from both the
ruling right-wing Likud Party and the oppositions of Labor and
Meretz.
</P>
<P>
The Kach Movement said the action was in retaliation for a
decision of the Israeli Knesset (Parliament) to remove the
memorial they erected for Baruch Goldstein.
</P>
<P>
Goldstein shot dead 29 Palestinian Muslim prayers in the Tomb
of Patriarch (Ibrahim Mosque called by Muslims) in Hebron in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Knesset approved Monday a bill that bans building memorials
for anyone who carried out an act of terror.
</P>
<P>
Rabin, chief architect of the Israeli-Arab peace process, was
gunned down by Jewish rightist Yigal Amir in November 1995 at a
Tel Aviv peace rally. Amir is now serving life sentence for the
assassination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
