<HEADLINE> Cypriot FM: Cyprus Must Be Reunified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot Foreign Minister
Ioannis Kasoulides Tuesday stressed that the only settlement of
the Cyprus question is to reunify the island based on the United
Nations resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides' comments were in response to a statement by
Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz, who recently told former
Greek premier Constantinos Mitsotakis that Turkish officials have
come to the conclusion that division is the sole solution in
Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus "rejects categorically any notion of accepting the fait
accompli resulting from the 1974 Turkish invasion," Kasoulides
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
He also dismissed emphatically any idea of "readjusting the
so-called borders in Cyprus and any idea of part of Cyprus
joining the European Union (EU)."
</P>
<P>
Cyprus will begin the accession talks with the EU this year.
</P>
<P>
"The country's borders are its coastline and its application
for EU relates to the entire island," the Cypriot foreign minister
added.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has remained divided since 1974 when Turkey landed its
troops and took over the northern third of the Mediterranean
island to protect the Turkish minorities after a failed coup by
the Greek Cypriots seeking union with Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
