for them to show that China can be a rock in the uncertain Asian
world," he said.
</P>
<P>
He quoted Chinese officials as saying that if the Asian
economic and financial crisis had come 10 years ago, it would have
blocked the economic reform in China. If it had arrived a few
years ago, China would have been entangled into the "same spiral
as Southeast Asia."
</P>
<P>
"In the present situation, China estimates that it can resist
and that its reforms are irreversible," he said. 
