<HEADLINE> Kuwait Bracing for Possible Emergency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait has taken
precautions to ward off possible emergency resulting from the
standoff between Iraq and the United States, the Kuwaiti News
Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti armed forces have raised its level of readiness to
face any actions that Iraq might take against Kuwait, Kuwaiti
Defense Ministry senior official Abdullah Al-Kandari told the news
agency.
</P>
<P>
Facing the tension caused by "Iraq's refusal to implement U.N.
Security Council resolutions," the Kuwaiti armed forces have been
on high alert, Al-Kandari said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has barred the United Nations Special Commission from
inspecting presidential palaces suspected of hiding secretive
weapons programs.
</P>
<P>
The commission is to certify the elimination of Iraq's nuclear,
chemical and biological weapons before the crippling economic
sanctions imposed on Iraq by U.N. Security Council seven years ago
can be lifted.
</P>
<P>
The United States has threatened to take military actions to
force Iraq to grant unrestricted access to U.N. arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has called for a peaceful solution to the crisis. But it
affirmed support to U.S. military actions against Iraq if
diplomatic efforts end in failure.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Kuwaiti Civil Defense Council has been
evaluating the current situation in the region to take necessary
measures to ensure public safety in any emergency.
</P>
<P>
And Health Minister Abdel Khaled Al-Sebeih has ordered the
medical emergency committee to review its stand-by plan. 
</P>
