<HEADLINE> Pak Stands by Commitment to Kashmiris: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 4 (Xinhua) -- President Rafiq Tarar said
Wednesday that Pakistan stands by its unwavering commitment to the
people of Kashmir in support of their right to determine their own
destiny.
</P>
<P>
In a message on the eve of the "Kashmir Solidarity Day," Tarar
said the day marks the commitment of the entire Pakistani nation
to the just demand of the people of Kashmir for the exercise of
the right of self-determination as pledged by the United Nations
and the international community.
</P>
<P>
"It is a solemn reminder to the world at large that the
Kashmiri people continue to be denied their fundamental rights,"
the message added.
</P>
<P>
Their rights must be honored and their dignity must be
respected, the president reiterated.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said in his message on
the occasion that the Pakistani government and people will
continue to extend all possible moral, political, diplomatic and
humanitarian support to the Kashmiris in their legitimate
struggle.
</P>
<P>
"The Kashmir dispute is the underlying cause of regional
tension and instability," said Sharif, adding that "a just and
fair settlement of the Kashmir dispute would permit the people of
the region to live in peace with dignity and honor and allow them
to focus on the pressing need for socioeconomic development."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan remains committed to the full implementation of the
resolutions on the Kashmir dispute passed by the U.N. Security
Council, the prime minister said.  
</P>
