Demirel Wednesday expressed his hope that the Iraqi crisis should
be solved through diplomatic efforts.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters at the presidential palace, Demirel said
the Iraqi crisis is "very grave" and Iraq must understand the
"gravity of the issue."
</P>
<P>
He said U.S. President Bill Clinton had sent him a letter on
the latest developments of the Iraqi crisis and he had given the
letter to the Turkish government, but declining to disclose the
content of the letter.
</P>
