Turkey Marc Parris conveyed Clinton's letter to Demirel late
Tuesday night. In his letter, Clinton sought Turkey's support in
case Washington launches a new military strike against Iraq,
according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said the U.S.-Turkish friendship is based on "the two
countries' solidarity in the Gulf region," adding that whether
this relationship will continue depends on Turkey's attitude,
according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Demirel admitted that he had asked his Foreign
Minister Ismail Cem to send a message to Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein. However, he also refused to detail on the content.
</P>
<P>
Cem left here for Baghdad Wednesday afternoon carrying a
"moderation" proposal from Demirel regarding the escalating crisis
between the United States and Iraq. 
