<HEADLINE> New Funding System Helps More People to Buy Own Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The Public Housing Fund, a new
funding system developed in recent years in Shanghai, has enabled
an increasing number of local residents to purchase their own
apartments.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, some 83,000 urban families in Shanghai have bought
their residential homes with 4.6 billion yuan in loans from the
fund.
</P>
<P>
More than 600,000 workers have purchased the property rights to
their homes which used to belong to the State.
</P>
<P>
The system was adopted in 1991. Since then, more than 95
percent of work units and their staff members have joined the
fund. So far, the city has collected 16.27 billion yuan for the
fund, which accounts for 20 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Employees whose work units have joined the fund now pay 6
percent of their wage to the fund and are able to get soft loans
in return.
</P>
<P>
The new system has also encouraged local banks to provide
mortgage loans for individuals. The Shanghai Branch of the China
Construction Bank alone granted local residents 3 billion yuan in
mortgage loans.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the city's management center of the Public
Housing Fund told Xinhua that in 1998 the fund is expected to
raise 5.8 billion yuan and to offer 5 billion yuan in mortgage
loans for local individual home buyers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
