<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Land Fund Close to 8 Billion Patacas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The Land Fund of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR) has come to almost 8 billion
patacas (about 1 billion U.S. dollars), the Macao Daily News
reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Yang Runzhen, chief of the Chinese side of the Sino-Portuguese
Land Group, told the newspaper that the fund would reach 10
billion patacas (about 1.25 billion dollars) by 1999 if the Macao
government collected the debt developers owe to it promptly.
</P>
<P>
Yang noted that the Chinese side has taken extra care in the
investment of the fund and the investment has not been affected by
the Asian currency crisis.
</P>
<P>
The fund is of vital importance to the future Macao SAR
government since no treasury reserve has been established so far,
she stressed.
</P>
<P>
Set up 10 years ago, the Sino-Portuguese Land Group handles
Macao's land contracts and related affairs on behalf of the
governments of China and Portugal. Its mission will wind up by
December 19, 1999. 
</P>
