<HEADLINE> AL Chief Arrives in Amman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Arab League (AL) Secretary
General Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Meguid arrived here Wednesday en route
to Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
He is on a mission trying to mediate a peaceful solution to the
crisis of arms inspection between Iraq and the United Nations
Special Commission (UNSCOM), which is in charge of eliminating
Iraq's weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
The AL chief told Jordanian Foreign Minister Fayez Tarawneh,
who greet him at the airport, that the standoff must be ended
through diplomatic efforts, not military actions.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the U.S. threat of military actions to
force Iraq to grant the UNSCOM free access to any inspection sites.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid is scheduled to leave for Baghdad later in the
day. He will join Russian and French special envoys to try to
persuade Iraqi President Saddam Hussein to take a flexible stance
to avert a catastrophe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
