<HEADLINE> New Zealand Holds Chile to Goalless Draw in Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The visiting World Cup
qualifier Chile was held by New Zealand to a goalless draw in a
friendly in Auckland on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Midway through the second half, Chile's striker Rodrigo Barrera
met a cross and headed into the net from close range but was
judged offside.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later New Zealand conceded a freekick from 20 meters
out and a well-struck shot over the defensive wall by substitute
Jose Luis Sierra beat All Whites goalkeeper Jason Batty but hit
the bar.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand, who have only qualified once for the World Cup
back in 1982, might even have taken a shock lead in the seventh
minute. But a crisp downward header from Danny Hay was just tipped
around the post by goalkeeper Marcelo Ramirez.  
</P>
