<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
fell 52 HK dollars Wednesday to close at 2,729 HK dollars a tael,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 296.05 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 5.67 U.S. dollars down from the previous close at Monday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar to 7.7377 HK dollars. 
</P>
