<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Expresses Deep Concern over Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Tung Chee Hwa has expressed
deep concern about a fire in Kwun Tong, Kowloon, Wednesday morning
which resulted in four deaths and a number of injuries.
</P>
<P>
Tung also extended his regards to families of the victims and
the injured in the No. 3 alarm fire that broke out in a composite
building in Shung Yan Street, Kwun Tong, at 5:22 a.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the Fire Service Department has set up an
investigation team to look into the cause of the fire and the
reason for the large number of casualties.
</P>
<P>
"Our priority now is to provide medical treatment for the
injured and assistance to the affected households," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
The Security Bureau and relevant departments are pitching their
efforts to follow up on the case, he added. The fire was put out
early Wednesday morning.  
</P>
</TEXT>
