<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Armenian Parliament Accepts President's Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The National Assembly of Armenia
accepted President Levon Ter-Petrosyan's resignation Wednesday
with 111 votes for, 36 against and 3 abstentions.
</P>
<P>
ITAR-TASS news agency reported that assembly speaker Babken
Araktsyan, supporter of the president, has also asked to step down.
</P>
<P>
Lately Ter-Petrosyan was criticized for what his opponents
described a "defeatist" position on the settlement of the
Nagorno-Karabakh problem.
</P>
<P>
Under the Armenian constitution, presidential elections
will be held 40 days after the president's resignation, and during
the vacant time, assembly speaker assumes presidential duty.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said Prime Minister Robert Kocharyan, who
gets support from the assembly majority Erkrapa group, has already
begun assuming the presidential duty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
