<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Issues Investment Licenses to 4,026 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority has announced that some 4,026 projects with an
aggregate capital of 33.9 billion Birr (about 4.9 billion US
Dollars) have been issued with investment licenses.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the House of People's Representatives
Tuesday, Tadesse Haile, General Manager of the Ethiopian Investment
Authority said, 788 projects, which account for 19.6 percent of
the total approved, have gone into operation with a combined
capital of 5.2 billion Birr (about 750 million Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Tadesse said these investment ventures have so far created job
opportunities for about 35,900 people since 1992 when the
Investment Code was issued.
</P>
<P>
Referring to foreign investment in the country, Tadesse said
foreign investment still accounts for about 6.6 billion Birr
(about 950 million Dollars) or 19.5 percent of the total approved
projects.
</P>
<P>
A number of measures were being taken to promote
multi-sectoral investment activities, he said, adding that "among
the measures aimed at encouraging foreign capital participation,
the Ethiopian government is acceding to bilateral and
multilateral investment guarantee agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
