<HEADLINE> Uganda Gets New Weather Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Meteorology Department
has received new meteorology equipments from Japan and Italy and
installed them in the southern city Entebbe, The Monitor reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The new equipments include a television weather presentation
studio and primary data user satellite receiver which will enable
Ugandan specialists to receive cloud images throughout the
country every 30 minutes and to improve visual delivery of
weather forecasts to the public.
</P>
<P>
Eliphaz Bazira, Acting Meteorology Commissioner, said the
equipments are vital for the collection of weather data and
delivery of weather forecast to serve agriculture, tourism,
transport and communications.
</P>
<P>
The new equipments were launched on January 23 by Gerald
Sendaula, Ugandan Minister of Natural Resources.
</P>
<P>
The United Kingdom also donated a 20,000-Pound (some 34
million U.S. Dollars) worth of studio to Uganda last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
