<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Silver Price Soars to Record High in Nine Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Silver price soared to
nine-year record high Tuesday, as stock of the metal dropped to
nearly 13-year low, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
On New York Mercantile Exchange, silver futures gained 36.7
cents to end at 6.615 US dollars an ounce Tuesday, after seeing a
new contract high at 6.630 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Silver price has been on the rise since July 1997. Reports
said that a major factor behind the recent rally in silver is that
demand has been outpacing supply, as it has been for the past
eight years.
</P>
<P>
New York Mercantile Exchange stock of silver dropped to 103.77
million ounces Monday, the lowest level since May 1985, according
to market analysts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
