<HEADLINE> China Schedules Large Treasury Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 4 (Xinhua) -- China plans to issue 125
billion yuan (15 billion US dollars) in certificate treasury bonds
between February 20 and October 31, the Ministry of Finance
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The issue will include 75 billion yuan in three-year bonds with
an annual coupon rate of 7.11 percent, and 50 billion yuan in
five-year bonds bearing an annual coupon rate of 7.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
The registered bonds on offer cannot be traded on the stock
market.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled bond issue will be the nation's first in 1998.
</P>
<P>
China issued treasury bonds valued at 241.2 billion yuan in
1996, including certificate bonds totalling 164.33 billion
yuan. The redemption of bonds maturing last year is basically
complete. 
</P>
</TEXT>
