<HEADLINE> U.S. Businessman Holds Million OUnces of Silver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, February 3 (Xinhua) -- An American businessman
dislcosed Tuesday that his company keeps a stock of nearly 130
million ounces of silver since last July.
</P>
<P>
Warren Buffett, chairman of Berkshire Hathaway Inc., said his
company has bought 129.7 million ounces of the precious metal
since July 1997 in anticipation that its price would rise as
demand outpaces supply.
</P>
<P>
The amount is more than inventories currently on hand at New
York Mercantile Exchange warehouses, which dropped to 103.77
million ounces Monday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came as silver prices soared to nine-year
highs Tuesday. Silver price has been on the rise since July
1997. Market analysts said a major factor behind the recent rally
in silver is that demand has been outpacing supply as it has for
the past eight years.
</P>
<P>
Others complain that there are investors who have been
manipulating the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
