<HEADLINE> Fish Fossils Discovered in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Archeologists working in north
China's Shanxi Province have unearthed fish fossils dating back
some 400 million years.
</P>
<P>
The fossils, found in Pingyao County, belong to the Devonian
Period in the Middle Palaeozoic Era, according to archeologists.
</P>
<P>
The two major fossils measure some two meters in length.
</P>
<P>
Archeologists say fossils will provide valuable information
about the geography, biology and environment in ancient times.
</P>
