<HEADLINE> New Book to Chronicle Jiang Zemin's US Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The World Affairs Press is
preparing for the Friday release of a new book covering Chinese
President Jiang Zemin's state visit to the United States,
according to an announcement made during today's joint press
conference held by the Chinese Foreign Ministry and the publisher.
</P>
<P>
The book entitled "Building the Sino-US Constructive Strategic
Partnership -- President Jiang Zemin's State Visit to the United
States" includes the Sino-US Joint Statement, President Jiang's
important lectures and speeches, an editorial and reports carried
in the People's Daily, and various remarks made by President
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The work features Chinese and English versions of most speeches
and documents, and includes selected photographs snapped during
the visit.  
</P>
