<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 222.90
points, or 2.12 percent, to close at 10,302.61 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The shares of commercial and industry, properties, utilities
and finance dropped 4.05 percent, 3.63 percent, 1.22 percent and
0.49 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, H shares -- China's State-owned enterprises listed
on the Hong Kong bourse -- went down 2.18 percent and red chips
fell 1.52 percent.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's turnover was 11,114 million HK dollars (1,425
million U.S. dollars), a reduction of 4,259 million HK dollars
(546 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index opened at 10,420.78 points in the morning,
a loss of 104.73 points, or 1.0 percent, from the close of the
previous trading day.
</P>
<P>
The shares fell 66.54 points, or 0.63 percent, to close at
10,458.97 at midday.
</P>
<P>
The stocks lost 53.09 points, or 0.50 percent, to close at
10,525.51 Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
