<HEADLINE> British Junior Foreign Minister Visits Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 4 (Xinhua) -- British junior foreign minister
Tony Lloyd met with Macedonian Foreign Minister Blagoj Handziski
in Macedonia Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Political dialogues between Macedonia and the European Union
(EU), their cooperation system and new developments in Macedonia
were discussed.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the two ministers also exchanged views on the
ethnic relations in Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Lloyd, speaking on behalf of Britain and the EU, urged the
Macedonian government to respect all ethnic groups and their
rights. He said he supported the political and economic reforms of
Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit in Macedonia starting Tuesday, the
British minister also met with Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov,
Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski, and leaders of major political
parties.
</P>
<P>
As part of his Balkan tour, Lloyd had visited Yugoslavia before
landing on Macedonia, and would arrive here soon.  
</P>
