<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong - China's Leading Consumer Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The total retail sales volume
for south China's Guangdong Province grew by 290 billion yuan in
1997, up 13 percent on the previous year's figure, with the retail
sales volume ranking first in China for 15 consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate for sales was 1.2 percent higher than the
national average when considering the decline in price hikes,
</P>
<P>
The 1997 growth was due to rapid economic growth over the past
two decades, with final figures expected to show that the
province's gross domestic product (GDP) hit 730 billion yuan, up
10.6 percent on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 per capita income of urban residents stood at 8,600
yuan, with the figure for rural areas standing at 3,375
yuan. Residents in Guangzhou, the provincial capital, spent an
average 10,000 yuan on consumer goods during the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
