<HEADLINE> Jamaican Delegation Welcomed to Olympic Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The Jamaican contigent which
inculcdes two bobsleigh teams was welcomed Wednesday to the Winter
Olympic Village by children of Susobana primary school who chanted "Go
Jamacia Go."
</P>
<P>
The delegation was also asked to take part in the traditional
Japanese custom of wishing someone good luck by painting in one eye of
the lucky face of a "daruma" doll. Upon victory, the team would then
get to paint in the other eye.
</P>
<P>
A six-member advance party of the Croatian delegation entered the
Village Wednesday morning and were presented colorful "Origami"
paper-folded necklaces by the children of Higashijo primary school.
The remainder of the Croatian delegation will be arriving over the
next couple of weeks, said Durko Dujmovic, Chief-de-Mission of the
delegation.
</P>
<P>
"We are not as strong in winter sports as we are in summer sports.
Our best hope is in our young Alpine skier, Janica Kostelic, who just
turned 16."
</P>
<P>
"She will definitely become a world Alpine ski champion," he
continued.
</P>
<P>
But Kostelic, who is making her debut at the Winter Olympics, is
not so confident. "I am just here to experience the atmosphere," she
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizing committee, 58 delegations have arrived
here for the games which will open on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
