<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Comments on Domestic, World Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We should say that China has much more knowledge about the
United States than the United States has about us. Only after they
had been to China did many U.S. senators find that the situation
is totally different from what they had in their minds. The visits
help change their minds; at least help increase their
understanding of the country, which is not an easy job at
all. More understanding will be a good to promoting Sino-US
relations. So we hope more Americans can come to China, to have a
look at both the developed regions and the underdeveloped
regions. Then they will get a comprehensive understanding of China.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Japanese relations have been developing smoothly in the
past 25 years since diplomatic relation between the two countries
were normalized. China and Japan are two countries that play
important roles in the Asian-Pacific region and the world. The
Joint Declaration Between the Government of the People's Republic
of China and the Government of Japan and the Treaty of Peace and
Friendship Between China and Japan are the foundation for the
development of Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
