<HEADLINE> German President to Visit S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 4 (Xinhua) -- German President Roman
Herzog will visit South Africa early next month, German
Ambassador Uwe Kaestner has said.
</P>
<P>
Herzog will meet South African President Nelson Mandela and
his deputy Thabo Mbeki in Cape Town before speaking before both
houses of the parliament, local daily Business Day Wednesday
quoted the German ambassador as reporting.
</P>
<P>
Several agreements are due to be signed by Herzog and Mandela,
including an investment protection pact, agreements on economic
development and cooperation, dual taxation, a sizable
contribution to low-income housing and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Herzog, who will be companied by a high-powered business
delegation, will also visit the Mercedes-Benz plant in East
London, Eastern Cape Province. He will be the first foreign head
of state to pay an official visit to the province since 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
