<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Supreme Court Favors Special Session of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's Supreme Court has
advised King Birendra to accept the recommendation by 96 MPs to
convene a special session of parliament to discuss their
no-confidence motion against the present government, informed
sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Six of the nine judges of the court's special bench including
the chief justice favored the recommendation by the legislators,
while the rest voted for the submission by Prime Minister Surya
Bahadur Thapa to dissolve parliament and hold mid-term elections,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
King Birendra is expected to announce his own decision at 0915
GMT, the sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
