<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes Annals of Ancient Tower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hunan People's Publishing
House recently published a work entitled The Annals of Yueyang
Tower about a famous ancient structure in central China's Hunan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The work contains 330,000 words and offers abundant historical
documents, records, photographs and literary works about the tower
which was constructed over 1,900 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The work outlines the culture, architecture, tourism, poetry,
and historical changes in the tower.
</P>
<P>
The three-storey wooden tower, which was built during the
Eastern Han Dynasty (25-220), stands near Dongting Lake in the
middle reaches of the Yangtze River.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
