<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Federation Asked to Improve Doping Record: German Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, February 4 (Xinhua) -- A leading German sports official
has on Wednesday asked Olympic leaders to mount pressure on
bodybuilding to clean up the sport.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee (IOC) executive board
member Thomas Bach said the doping record of the sport had to be
improved before it could be allowed full recognition.
</P>
<P>
Bodybuilding's international federation has just won
provisional recognition by the IOC.
</P>
<P>
"That is the advantage of giving recognition to a sport rather
than ignoring it. You can put more pressure on it in that way,"
Bach said.
</P>
<P>
The international federations of speedboating, motorcycling and
sumo wrestling have also been granted provisional recognition at
an IOC meeting before the Nagano Winter Olympics, which start this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
Provisional recognition just means federations accept certain
Olympic principles and allows the IOC to work more closely with
officials in the sport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
