<HEADLINE> China Exports More Machinery and Electronics Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Today's Economic Daily reported
that China's foreign trade volume for machinery and electronics
products totaled 118.6 billion US dollars for 1997, thereby
basically achieving the first-ever trade balance for said products.
</P>
<P>
China exported related products valued at 59.32 billion US
dollars during 1997, up 23 percent on the previous year, with
imports falling by 3.2 percent to 59.33 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 trade volume for machinery and electronics products
grew 8.3 percent and accounted for 36.5 percent of the nation's
total foreign trade volume of 325.06 billion US dollars. The
latter figure represented a 12.1 percent rise on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper reported that China will further improve its
import and export structure by encouraging the importation of
advanced technology and equipment. The country will also avoid
repetitive imports and will provide greater support for exports of
machinery and electronics products.
</P>
<P>
China will strive to export machinery and electronic products
valued at 60 billion US dollars during 1998 in order to promote
national economic growth, according to the newspaper.  
</P>
</TEXT>
