<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran: No Dialog With Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 4 (Xinhua) -- A senior Iranian official
Wednesday reiterated that Iran will not recognize Israel and
rejects any contact with it.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here Wednesday morning, Vice
President and head of the Environmental Protection Organization
Masoumeh Ebtekar rejected any contact or dialog with the Israeli
government.
</P>
<P>
"There are Jews in Iran and we respect them," she said, adding
that Iran also has no problems with the Israeli Jews.
</P>
<P>
Ebtekar once again denied her interview with the Israeli daily
Yedioth Ahronoth, expressing "surprise and regret" that the
Israeli newspaper made such baseless claim.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli daily claimed Sunday that Ebtekar announced her
support for a dialog between Iran and Israel in "the first
interview by an Iranian political figure with an Israeli
newspaper."
</P>
<P>
However, the Iranian vice president immediately denied such an
interview, saying that "raising such unfounded claims is a clear
example of mischief by the Zionist news circles."
</P>
<P>
Referring to her stance towards the United States, Ebtekar
said "we do not have any problems with the American people, but we
do have problems with the U.S. politicians."
</P>
<P>
She criticized the U.S. military presence in the Persian Gulf
region, terming the presence of foreign warships in the Gulf as
one of the main factors of the pollution in the region.
</P>
<P>
"It is our great concern that foreign warships released
chemical pollutants in the Persian Gulf," she said, adding
that all the ships in the international waters should respect
international norms, including laws on environmental protection.
</P>
</TEXT>
