<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Four Asian referees from Japan,
Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates and Thailand have been
chosen to officiate at this summer's World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Pirom Un-Prasert of Thailand leads the pack which also include
Abdul Rahman Al Zeid of Saudi Arabia, Ali Mohamed Bujsaim of the
United Arab Emirates and Masayoshi Okada from Japan.
</P>
