<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA -- Cuban President Fidel Castro lashed out at the
longstanding United States embargo against the country on Monday
and reiterated that Washington should end it as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"Cuba does not demand humanitarian aid from the United
States. It demands an end to the economic war against our people,
and that it respects our right to develop ourselves economically
and trade freely with all the people of the world," Castro said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark in a live television address to analyze Pope
John Paul II's first visit to Cuba on January 21-25.
(Cuba-US-Embargo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- A U.S. Marine warplane hit and cut a cable car line in
northern Italy Tuesday, causing a cable car to crash into the
hillside with all the 20 people aboard killed.
</P>
<P>
Italy's ANSA news agency reported that the accident occurred in
Cavalese City of Trento Province in northern Italy and that the
warplane landed back at its base with the crew apparently unaware
of what had happened.
</P>
<P>
The cable car was traveling from the town of Cavalese to the
top of Cermis mountain, the site of a popular local ski resort in
northern Italy, when the warplane hit and cut the cable car line
with its tail surface, ANSA said. (Italy-Cable Car Crash-Update)
</P>
