<HEADLINE> China's Island Province Builds More Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, February 4 (Xinhua) -- China's island province of
Hainan recently completed a 60.2-km section of expressway linking
Jiusuo with Sanya, local sources report.
</P>
<P>
Hainan's transport conditions have not been good because of
mountains in its central and western areas, greatly hindering
economic development. So, for the past several years, the island
has tried many fund-raising methods and has raised a lot of
capital for road construction.
</P>
<P>
The four-lane expressway in its western part is 366 km
long. The northern section, from Haikou, the provincial capital,
to Yangpu, is 105.7 km long and was completed last March. The
section from Yangpu to Basuo is expected to be finished later this
year.
</P>
<P>
Preparatory work on another section of the western expressway,
from Basuo to Jiusuo, 93.3 km long, is underway. The eastern part,
268 km long, was completed in late 1995. An expansion of the
northern section, from Haikou to Qionghai, started in late 1996
and is expected to be finished in March.
</P>
<P>
Work on the southeastern part, from Qionghai to Lingshui, will
soon start. The whole beltway will be completed by the year 2000,
local officials say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
