<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Implement Silk Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's Textile Ministry
will implement a World Bank-financed project from next month to
promote silk production in the country, a local newspaper reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 1.4 billion taka (30 million U.S. dollar) silk foundation
project is aimed at boosting production of quality silk worm,
ensuring training for growers and helping farmers from
cooperatives, the Daily Star said.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, the main field-level work will be in the
silk producing zones of Rajshahi, Jamalpur, Sherpur and Manikganj,
and the head office of the project will be in the capital Dhaka,
the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's silk industry needs some 250 tons of raw silk per
year, but the country can only produce about 30 tons yearly.
</P>
