<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Liaoning Industrializes Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has scored considerable achievements in industrializing
its agriculture in the last few years.
</P>
<P>
Of the 106 provincial-level projects selected for
experimentation in agricultural industrialization, 19 have been
completed while another 14 are in progress.
</P>
<P>
The incremental output value of the completed projects is
predicted at 4.7 billion yuan each year. When all the projects are
completed in 2000, the total incremental output value should hit
26.7 billion yuan, about half of Liaoning's expected total
agricultural output value that year.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that agriculture in Liaoning, China's largest
industrial center, has entered a new period of industrialization,
a period of deep processing of farm produce.
</P>
<P>
Official figures indicate that agricultural industrialization
has accounted for 30 percent of the increased income of farmers in
Liaoning. By the year 2000, 60 percent of the increased income
will result from agricultural industrialization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
