<HEADLINE> Russia Sees Foreign Trade Volume Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Russia's foreign trade volume
reached 153.6 billion U.S. dollars last year, up 1.5 percent from
that of 1996, said the National Statistics Bureau on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Export was 86.7 billion dollars, down 2.7 percent in the
period, while import was 66.9 billion dollars, dropping 7.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
The import of industrial equipment saw an increase of 19
percent and export, 2.5 percent, showing signs of recovery in this
economic sector.
</P>
<P>
In the year, Russia's trade volume with the Commonwealth of
Independent States decreased from 22.5 percent of 1996 to 21
percent. 
