<HEADLINE> Hungary Welcomes Denmark's Approval of Its NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian Foreign Minister
Laszlo Kovacs on Tuesday welcomed Danish parliament's approval of
the accession of Hungary, Poland and the Czech Republic to the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
The Danish parliament passed the resolution earlier Tuesday,
the first NATO member country to approve the document.
</P>
<P>
Kovacs told the Czech news agency that the Danish move
represented the start of the final phase for the three Central and
East European countries' membership in the trans-Atlantic
alliance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
