<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovakia Seizes Massive Marijuana Haul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia police arrested four
alleged drug traffickers and seized 12.9 tons of marijuana in a
recent drug-fighting operation, the Czech news agency reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The police took possession of the marijuana on January 30 in
the town of Mojmirovce. It was concealed in a container in a truck
and was disguised as glassware.
</P>
<P>
The drug, valued at 2.8 billion korun (82.3 million U.S
dollars), was smuggled into Slovakia from Columbia via Panama, the
United States, Germany and the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
The arrested suspects include two Slovakians, one Columbian and
one Czech, said a police source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
