 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The newspaper frontpaged a story on how the production base
of the Tibetan Military Area Command has developed high-yield
agriculture on the Tibet Plateau, known as the "forbidden zone to
life".
</P>
<P>
-- China has allocated 1.6 billion yuan in developing normal
education since 1991 in addition to 100 million US dollars of
loans from the World Bank and some 9 million US dollars from
related organizations of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
By 1996, China had established 232 normal schools of higher
learning and 893 secondary normal schools. From 1992 to 1996, the
total number of graduates from the normal schools reached 2.123
million.
</P>
<P>
Overseas Edition of "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China has reported rapid growth in its marine economy in
recent years, with the total output value in this sector exceeding
280 billion yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Bureau of Oceanography, by the year
2000, the total output value of the country in this sector will
top 500 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China hopes that all parties concerned will take a
restrained and flexible attitude to avoid worsening of the Iraq
crisis, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said in
Beijing Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said China opposes the use of force or threat of force and
advocates a peaceful settlement of the crisis. China also supports
the diplomatic efforts for the purpose by all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
-- The newspaper frontpaged a story on how Anhui Province, in
east China, is rebuilt after a devastating flood in 1991.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the province's total gross domestic product reached
267 billion yuan, three times the figure of 1991, with the annual
increase rate standing at 16.6 percent, which is five percentage
points higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
" China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A total of 38,000 live chickens will have been transported
to Hong Kong from the Chinese mainland by the coming Saturday
since an epidemic of bird flu swept the area late last
year. 
