<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers Wednesday:
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times
</P>
<P>
-- Six top executives of the Steel Authority of India Limited
have been killed in a company plane crash in Madhya Pradesh Monday
night.
</P>
<P>
The Hindu
</P>
<P>
-- The Bharatiya Janata Party's (BJP) 55-page manifesto issued
here Tuesday keeps Hindutva intact while it promises to move
towards making India a declared nuclear state.
</P>
<P>
The Statesman
</P>
<P>
-- At least 50 people including 39 policemen were injured when
members of two communities clashed in east Delhi on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Observer
</P>
<P>
-- The Reserve Bank of India on Tuesday announced fresh
relaxation in rules governing operations of merchant banking
companies in the non-banking finance company sector.  
</P>
</TEXT>
