<HEADLINE> United States to Face Paraguay in Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 3 (Xinhua) -- World Cup qualifiers the
United States and Paraguay will face each other in a friendly
international in San Diego next month.
</P>
<P>
The United States Soccer Federation said on Tuesday the match
is scheduled on March 14.
</P>
<P>
The United States will play in Group F while Paraguay compete
in Group D in the World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
The United States are currently playing in the CONCACAF Gold
Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
On the schedule for friendlies, the team will play World Cup
qualifiers Netherlands on February 21 in Miami and meet Begium on
February 25 in Brussels. 
</P>
