<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WB Chief: Indonesia has Ability to pay Foreign Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Visiting World Bank President
James Wolfensohn expressed the hope Tuesday that Indonesia's
economy will quickly recover from its present crisis, saying he
thought the country does have the ability to pay its debts.
</P>
<P>
Wolfensohn arrived here Tuesday evening from Kuala Lumpur for a
three-day visit as part of a seven-day tour of Southeast Asian
countries including Thailand, Malaysia and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Wolfensohn will meet Indonesian President
Soeharto and other senior government officials on Wednesday,
official Antara News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He will also hold a closed-door meeting with 70 politicians,
economists, businessmen, environment experts and some
non-governmental organization officials.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank chief is scheduled to visit a labor-intensive
project in Jakarta financed by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
On January 15, Indonesia concluded agreements with the World
Bank's sister organization, the International Monetary Fund (IMF),
for an expanded assistance program worth some 40 billion US
dollars to fight the financial and monetary crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
