<HEADLINE> Thailand to consider Granting Citizenship to 1,100 Nepalese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will consider a
Nepalese government request for it to grant citizenship to 1,100
Nepalese nationals living in the country.
</P>
<P>
The National Security Council of Thailand will be asked to
consider the request made by Nepalese Foreign Minister Kamal
Thapa, who Tuesday discussed immigration issues with Thai interior
Minister Sanan Kachornprasart, a source at the Interior Ministry
was quoted Wednesday by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
The request has been sought in favor of a total of 1,103
Nepalese nationals who have been living in Thailand for more than
50 years.
</P>
<P>
Sanan has also promised to consider Thapa's request seeking
pardon for 26 Nepalese inmates convicted of minor crimes.
</P>
</TEXT>
