<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pioline Beaten in Marseille Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Fifth seed Cedric Pioline of
France had a shock exit in the first round of the Marseille ATP
tournament in Marseille, France, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Pioline, finalist in 1997 U.S. Open, lost to Mikael Tillstrom
of Sweden 7-6, 3-6, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
"It's the most tiring and culture shocking journey of the
season. You need some time to re-adapt," said Pioline, who lost to
eventual winner Petr Korda of Czech Republic in the fourth round
of the Australian Open a week ago.
</P>
<P>
Number three seed Sergi Bruguera beat fellow Spaniard Tomas
Carbonell 6-2 4-6 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Other seeds went through without much trouble on Tuesday, with
top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia beating Spain's Juan Albert
Viloca and second-seeded Dutch Richard Krajicek rolling over
Morocco's Karim Alami, both in straight sets.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten, fourth seed in Marseille, also had
an easy day beating Belgium's Filip Dewulf 6-2, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
