<DOCNO> XIE19980204.0265 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Illicit Poppy Plantations Destroyed in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 4 (Xinhua) -- Over 16,000 hectares of illicit
poppy plantations were destroyed in Myanmar's Shan state recently,
the New Light of Myanmar newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The plantations, in 17 townships of the state, were destroyed
by the local army units, police force in cooperation with regional
departments concerned between November 6 last year and January 22
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier official report, the Myanmar
authorities also uncovered and destroyed two more heroin
refineries in Kutkai area, northeastern Shan state, in January
following the seizure of 33 similar refineries in the state in
1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
