<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting of Jurists Will be Held in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Panama City, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Jurists from Panama, Cuba,
Jamaica, Dominican Republic and Mexico will gather February 17-18
to go over humanitarian international law issues in the region,
the Panamanian Chancery announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The head of the general direction of international organisms
and conferences of the Chancery, Edgar Spence said that the forum
that will take place in the Panamanian capital, will address
issues on the interchange of experiences on human rights.
</P>
<P>
The participants will also analyse the situation of the
refugees and displaced persons during the civil conflicts that
scourged Central America.
</P>
<P>
The commission of human rights of the attending countries and
the regional delegation for international committee of the Red
Cross for Central-America, Mexico and the Caribbean just to
mention some of the participants.
</P>
<P>
Spence declared that many jurists will attend such as the Swiss
Cristina Pellandini, the Chilean Hernan Salinas Burgos, the
Costa-Rican Tatiana Flores and Jose Luis Rodriguez-Villiasante,
director for the Humanitarian International Center for Spain.
</P>
<P>
There are some one thousand refugees living in Panama which
fled from domestic armed conflicts that scourged Centroamerica
during the 80's. 
</P>
</TEXT>
