<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Twenty Killed in Cable Car Crash in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were killed in a
cable car crash in northern Italy Tuesday, which came after a
U.S. navy warplane hit and cut the mountain cable way hanging the
cable car.
</P>
<P>
Italy's ANSA news agency reported that the accident occurred in
Cavalese City of Trento Province in northern Italy and that the
warplane landed back at its base with the crew apparently unaware
of what had happened.
</P>
<P>
Italian Defense Ministry sources in Rome said that when the
plane made an emergency landing at the NATO base at Aviano about
100 kilometers southeast of Rome, the pilot reported that he had
simply felt a "big bump."
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Marine Ea-6b electronic warplane, deployed at Aviano
for service with the U.N. Stabilization Force in Bosnia, was on a
scheduled training mission in the area, the Defense Ministry
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue teams sent to the area reported that the plane sliced
the cable with its tail surface, causing the car to crash into the
hillside with all the passengers and crew killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
