<HEADLINE> Greene Sets World Indoor 60m Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 3 (Xinhua) -- World 100 meters champion
Maurice Greene of the United States set an indoor world record of
6.39 seconds for the 60 meters here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He improved on the previous record of 6.41 seconds set by
compatriot Andre Cason at the same venue in 1992 and equalled by
Greene in Stuttgart, Germany, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But he said after the race that the aim in his mind was 6.37
seconds and hoped to achieve that later this season.
</P>
<P>
Greene is expected to run two more indoor 60 meters races, one
at the Millrose Games in New York on February 13 and the other in
Birmingham, England, on February 15.
</P>
<P>
His compatriot and training partner Jon Drummond finished
second in 6.50.
</P>
<P>
In the 60 meters hurdles races, American Allen Johnson ran the
fastest men's time in the world this year in 7.44 seconds, while
Jamaica's Michelle Freeman achieved the same in the women's event,
clocking 7.74.
</P>
<P>
In the men's long jump, the best mark of the year was improved
twice.
</P>
<P>
Portugal's Carlos Calado jumped 8.11 meters in the fourth round
but Jamaica's James Beckford leaped to 8.21 one round later for
the title. 
</P>
