<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 100 Million U.S. Dollar Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
approved a 100 million U.S. dollar Contractual Saving Structural
Adjustment Loan for Uruguay to help its pension system reform.
</P>
<P>
The loan will help the government implement the pension reform
by covering part of the short-run costs and widening the set of
investment opportunities available to the privately managed
pension funds.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to support measures to liberalize the
investment regime of the fund administrators, increase the
availability of private securities to match the growth of those
funds, and create incentives to promote cost consciousness and
transparency in reporting by pension fund administrators. 
</P>
