<HEADLINE> Volkswagen Achieves Record Vehicle Deliveries in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest carmaker
Volkswagen announced Tuesday that it has delivered a total of 4.26
million vehicles worldwide last year, up 7.3 percent from the
previous record year of 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued Tuesday by the
Wolfsburg-based company, increases had been achieved in almost all
regions.
</P>
<P>
With 2.49 million vehicles delivered in Western Europe, the
Volkswagen group said it had retained the position as the region's
market leader with a market share of 17.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
In Asian-Pacific region, including Japan, demand for new
vehicles has been dampened due to financial turmoil. Nevertheless,
the deliveries of Volkswagen vehicles still rose by 11.5 percent
to 371,500 units.
</P>
<P>
In North America, Volkswagen's deliveries also jump 13.0
percent to 273,300 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
For the current year, the company was expecting further
improvement from the 1997 performance, said Robert Buechelhofer, a
board member of the Volkswagen AG. 
</P>
</TEXT>
